social_posts.post_text: Vineyards, hammocks, and a breathtaking view of Mt. Hood - Steven and Lily's engagement session at Gorge Crest Vineyards was a dream come true! Check out the blog for all the stunning photos. Can't wait for their wedding this summer!

Excellence is in the details and this one takes the cake! 🍰✨ The Three Sisters mountains painted on this wedding cake in Bend are a beautiful reminder that it’s the little things that make a big impact. Don't be afraid to have fun with the details when planning your big day - it's these touches that make your wedding uniquely yours. Swipe through for some serious inspiration!

Come decorate with me and let’s fill our home with reminders of God’s faithfulness! Psalm 91 has been my go-to for comfort and strength. I’ve even memorized it to remind myself that the Lord is my refuge. Let’s create a space that not only looks beautiful but also uplifts our spirits with the goodness and grace of God ✨
We had the prettiest light for this beautiful couple! Isaias & Traci, I absolutely loved capturing your wedding!! ✨
Simple moments in Portland with Chris + Mandy🌲✨
some getting ready moments from the morning of Haley’s wedding 🤍

Have you ever wondered what photography equipment I use? I’m sharing part of my photography journey on my blog today and it’s written for anyone who’s ever been curious about my camera gear over the years 📸🫶🏻 link in bio
In the heart of the orchards with Stephen & Kayla 🤍🫶🏻🍃 new blog post featuring this stunning wedding!!

If you’re planning a proposal, I highly recommend having a photographer there to capture the moment! I loved photographing my bestfriend’s proposal last year! Kevin & Mikayla’s beautiful sunrise proposal is on the blog 💍☀️

It’s an amazing thing when God answers your prayer for a spouse!! Josh and Chelsie had each been praying for marriage and when they met, they knew it was an answer to this prayer! Just blogged this beautiful wedding of my friends, Chelsie and Josh ✨

I had the pleasure of photographing my best friend Jessica’s engagement photos with her now-husband Josh in the beautiful little town of Aurora, Oregon! Even though these photos are a little overdue since they’re already married, I’m still excited to share the beautiful memories we captured on the blog today 💕✨📸

I’m so excited to announce my two Thanksgiving sales for all of my clients! My first sale is on the custom albums designed by Julia Green Photography. I’m offering $200 off any 12x12 (design one) album! Please comment or DM me to receive the pricing guide with details on the process and the album covers you can select from. This sale will run for 2 weeks!

My second sale is on any Pic-Time gallery (prints, basic albums made by you, and holiday items). Check your emails because the Pic-Time deals discounts have been sent out!! Happy shopping 📸❤️

Studio sessions are some of my favorite because it’s in a controlled atmosphere where all the dynamics are set by me - the lighting, weather, mood, and atmosphere is controlled to bring out a consistent outcome! Overall, it makes a shoot more efficient! Enjoy these lovely photos of Stephen and Kayla!! I just loved my time with them 📸🤍
